<subSubSection id="AB90C1A9FFF8C470FF023BADFAF4FA34" box="[199,1379,1437,1461]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E3359222FFF8C470FF023BADFAF4FA34" blockId="1.[151,1436,789,1713]" box="[199,1379,1437,1461]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis id="D1FE4E30FFF8C470FF023BADFED9FA34" bold="true" box="[199,334,1437,1461]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Etymology.</emphasis>
Latin, ruber = red; suffix ceps, derived from caput = head; refers to the red color of the head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AB90C1A9FFF8C470FF023BF1FBDAF930" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E3359222FFF8C470FF023BF1FBDAF930" blockId="1.[151,1436,789,1713]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">
<emphasis id="D1FE4E30FFF8C470FF023BF1FEDBFA5B" bold="true" box="[199,332,1473,1498]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="248AE9A1FFF8C470FE933BF1FD59FA58" authority="Thomson, 1864" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[342,718,1473,1497]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hexoplon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venus">
<emphasis id="D1FE4E30FFF8C470FE933BF1FD9AFA58" box="[342,525,1473,1497]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Hexoplon venus</emphasis>
Thomson, 
<number id="55428005FFF8C470FD563BF1FD59FA58" box="[659,718,1473,1497]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" value="1864.0">1864</number>
</taxonomicName>
, occurring in 
<collectingCountry id="9B9DD2B2FFF8C470FCB73BF1FC74FA58" box="[882,995,1473,1497]" name="Colombia" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="9B9DD2B2FFF8C470FC373BF1FBF2FA58" box="[1010,1125,1473,1497]" name="Venezuela" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="9B9DD2B2FFF8C470FB673BF1FAD9FA58" box="[1186,1358,1473,1497]" name="French Guiana" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
, is the only species with similar elytral color as 
<taxonomicName id="248AE9A1FFF8C470FDB03BD6FC92FA7C" box="[629,773,1509,1533]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hexoplon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubriceps" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="D1FE4E30FFF8C470FDB03BD6FC92FA7C" box="[629,773,1509,1533]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">H. rubriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D1FE4E30FFF8C470FCCA3BD5FCFCFA7C" bold="true" box="[783,875,1509,1533]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CACDF34BFFF8C470FCCA3BD5FCFCFA7C" box="[783,875,1509,1533]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Both will key to couplet 
<quantity id="24723FC7FFF8C470FB5D3BD5FB43FA7C" box="[1176,1236,1509,1533]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.334" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" unit="in" value="21.0">21 in</quantity>
the key to South American species (
<bibRefCitation id="871BEFD3FFF8C470FE443839FDB8F9A0" author="Martins" box="[385,559,1545,1569]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" refString="Martins, U. R. (2006) Hexoplonini. In: Cerambycidae sul-americanos. Sao Paulo, Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia. v. 8, pp. 21 - 211." type="journal article" year="2006">
Martins, 
<number id="55428005FFF8C470FE373839FDB8F9A0" box="[498,559,1545,1569]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). They can be differentiated as follows: 
<taxonomicName id="248AE9A1FFF8C470FBFC383AFB46F9A0" box="[1081,1233,1545,1569]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hexoplon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubriceps" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="D1FE4E30FFF8C470FBFC383AFB46F9A0" box="[1081,1233,1545,1569]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">H. rubriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D1FE4E30FFF8C470FB26383AFAD0F9A3" bold="true" box="[1251,1351,1546,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="CACDF34BFFF8C470FB26383AFAD0F9A3" box="[1251,1351,1546,1570]" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a predominantly black prothorax; elytra with black band, curved in front before the extremity, oblique black fascia reaching the margin in the apical third of each elytron and femora and body ventrally black. In 
<taxonomicName id="248AE9A1FFF8C470FAC43862FAF0F9E8" box="[1281,1383,1618,1641]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hexoplon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venus">
<emphasis id="D1FE4E30FFF8C470FAC43862FAF0F9E8" box="[1281,1383,1618,1641]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="572">H. venus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: the prothorax, elytra, femora and ventral body are red; a red band before the elytra extremity, with its anterior margin straight, and the oblique black stripe in the middle of the elytra ending at the margin.
</paragraph>
